results.name: Rectangular array, r(n,k), by antidiagonals:  the interspersion associated with the fractal sequence A249727.
comment: r(n,k) is the position of the k-th occurrence of n in A249727.  Every positive integer occurs exactly once, and each row is interspersed by each other row, except for initial terms.
mathematica: Table[r[n - k + 1, k], {n, 15}, {k, n, 1, -1}] // Flatten  (* A272616 sequence*)
results.author: _Clark Kimberling_, May 14 2016
